OH THANK YOU GUYS, THANKS!

24:03.529 --> 24:05.052
OH THAT'S SO GREAT!

24:05.182 --> 24:06.053
YOU GUYS REALLY THINK SO?

24:06.183 --> 24:07.271
-YOU WERE UNBELIEVABLE!

24:07.402 --> 24:09.056
I CAN'T BELIEVE
IT, I ACTUALLY--

24:09.186 --> 24:10.623
I LOVE COUNTRY MUSIC!

24:10.753 --> 24:12.451
-SEE, I TOLD YA!

24:12.581 --> 24:13.626
ALL YOU HAD TO DO WAS LISTEN
ONCE, AND YOU'D BE HOOKED.

24:15.018 --> 24:17.673
JESSE, DID YOU REALLY
THINK IT WAS GOOD?

24:17.804 --> 24:19.719
-HEY I MEAN WHAT I SAY
AND I SAY WHAT I MEAN.

24:19.849 --> 24:21.285
AS A MATTER OF FACT, I
GOT A PROPOSAL FOR YOU.

24:21.982 --> 24:23.940
I'M HEADED TO
VEGAS IN A FEW DAYS

24:24.463 --> 24:26.465
AND I THINK THAT YOU'RE JUST
WHAT I NEED TO OPEN THE SHOW.

24:27.117 --> 24:28.858
-YES!
-YOU'RE KIDDING!

24:28.989 --> 24:30.381
-HOW WOULD YOU LIKE
TO JOIN MY TOUR?

24:30.512 --> 24:32.601
-ME, OPEN YOUR SHOW?

24:34.081 --> 24:35.648
-OH I'M SO PROUD OF YOU!

24:35.778 --> 24:37.040
-SO GREAT.

24:37.171 --> 24:38.215
THANK YOU SO MUCH
FOR EVERYTHING.

24:38.346 --> 24:39.303
-STEPHANIE: COME
ON, LET'S DANCE!

24:39.434 --> 24:40.391
-ALL RIGHT, ALL RIGHT, I'M IN.

24:40.522 --> 24:41.567
-I'M NOT GONNA LET YOU DOWN.

24:41.697 --> 24:42.655
I CAN'T WAIT.

24:42.785 --> 24:43.699
I GOTTA GO CALL MY MOM AND DAD.

24:43.830 --> 24:44.874
THANKS.

24:47.616 --> 24:50.489
-[SLOW COUNTRY MUSIC]

25:00.237 --> 25:01.456
-I KNOW WE DIDN'T
HAVE ANY LUCK TODAY

25:01.587 --> 25:03.458
FINDING JACKSON AND CRYSTAL,

25:04.328 --> 25:05.721
BUT WE'RE GONNA FIND THEM.

25:06.809 --> 25:08.158
I PROMISE.

25:08.811 --> 25:11.292
-I GOT JUST SO MUCH THAT
I WANNA SAY TO BOTH OF 'EM.

25:12.075 --> 25:13.642
I JUST PRAY THAT
I GET THE CHANCE.

25:14.817 --> 25:15.862
-YOU WILL.

25:19.822 --> 25:21.041
-EXCUSE ME, STEPHANIE.

25:21.171 --> 25:22.651
I PROMISED TO SAVE
MITCH A DANCE.

25:24.305 --> 25:27.003
-[LAUGHS] UH, WHERE'S HOBIE?

25:27.656 --> 25:28.527
-I DON'T KNOW.

25:29.484 --> 25:30.354
-I'LL BE RIGHT BACK.

25:41.801 --> 25:42.976
WHAT'S WRONG?

25:46.545 --> 25:47.807
-BRIDGETTE CALLED ME A DORK.

25:47.937 --> 25:49.504
-OH MAN, I'M SORRY.

25:50.026 --> 25:51.680
FORGET ABOUT THAT.

25:51.811 --> 25:54.030
COME ON, I BOUGHT YOU YOUR
FAVORITE, A&W CREAM SODA.

25:54.553 --> 25:56.946
LET'S GO OUT AND SHOW THOSE
GUYS HOW TO LINE DANCE, HUH?

25:57.077 --> 25:57.904
-ALL RIGHT.

26:01.690 --> 26:04.475
-[GENTLE MUSIC]

26:06.956 --> 26:08.175
-[KNOCKING]

26:08.305 --> 26:09.219
-HEY, JESSE, COME ON IN.

26:09.350 --> 26:10.699
-HEY, MITCH.

26:10.830 --> 26:12.179
-SADIE WAS UNREAL
LAST NIGHT, WASN'T SHE?

26:12.309 --> 26:13.136
-OH BOY SHE WAS GREAT.

26:13.267 --> 26:14.964
I WAS REALLY IMPRESSED.

26:15.095 --> 26:17.750
I'LL TELL YOU, I DON'T KNOW
HOW TO THANK YOU FOR THIS.

26:19.578 --> 26:21.841
BUT I GUESS YOU KNOW, DON'T YOU?

26:21.971 --> 26:24.408
-YEAH, I KNOW
EXACTLY HOW YOU FEEL.

26:25.322 --> 26:26.976
-I MISS MY BOY, MITCH.

26:27.586 --> 26:30.153
LAST NIGHT SEEING
YOU WITH HOBIE.

26:30.284 --> 26:31.502
MAN, HE'S A GREAT KID.

26:32.242 --> 26:34.418
I SURE DO MISS THOSE
FATHER-SON TIMES.

26:34.549 --> 26:36.682
-WELL I GUESS
THE POINT HERE IS,

26:38.379 --> 26:39.902
WHAT YOU'RE WILLING
TO DO TO GET HIM BACK.

26:40.816 --> 26:42.775
-YOU MEAN LIKE WHAT AM
I WILLING TO GIVE UP?

26:44.298 --> 26:45.429
-YEAH, SOMETHING LIKE THAT.

26:46.039 --> 26:48.215
-MITCH I WORKED HARD
FOR MY SINGING CAREER.

26:48.737 --> 26:50.043
I MEAN IT'S MY JOB
TO BE ON THE ROAD.

26:50.739 --> 26:52.306
-I DON'T MEAN TO
BE OUT OF LINE HERE,

26:53.089 --> 26:54.395
BUT I'M FAMILIAR
WITH YOUR MUSIC.

26:54.525 --> 26:56.223
I MEAN I GOT MOST
OF YOUR RECORDS.

26:56.353 --> 26:58.051
THEY CHART GOLD, PLATINUM.

26:58.573 --> 26:59.487
YOU'VE ALREADY MADE IT.

27:00.531 --> 27:02.882
YOU KNOW, MAYBE IT'S NOT THAT
MUCH TO ASK FOR

27:03.404 --> 27:05.319
CRYSTAL TO HAVE YOU CUT
DOWN ON A FEW ROAD TRIPS.

27:06.233 --> 27:08.409
-WELL WE AIN'T EVER BEEN
VERY GOOD AT COMPROMISING.

27:10.019 --> 27:11.455
-SIT DOWN FOR A
SECOND, WILL YOU?

27:16.025 --> 27:19.899
YOU KNOW, JESSE, I WISH I HAD
SOMEBODY TO COMPROMISE WITH.

27:21.378 --> 27:22.989
I MEAN, I'M DOING
IT ALL WITH HOBIE.

27:23.119 --> 27:26.383
DEALING WITH ALL OF HIS
PROBLEMS, HEALING ALL HIS HURTS.

27:28.168 --> 27:30.257
LAST NIGHT AT DENIM AND
DIAMONDS, THIS LITTLE GIRL

27:30.387 --> 27:31.475
CAME UP TO HIM AND
CALLED HIM A DORK.

27:32.476 --> 27:35.262
I WOULD'VE GIVEN ANYTHING IF
HIS MOTHER COULD'VE BEEN THERE

27:35.392 --> 27:37.090
TO HOLD HIM AND COMFORT
HIM AND TALK TO HIM.

27:37.743 --> 27:39.266
-WELL CRYSTAL IS
A WONDERFUL MOTHER

27:39.396 --> 27:40.833
SO I GUESS JACKSON'S
LUCKY FOR THAT.

27:42.922 --> 27:43.879
-HE NEEDS A DAD TOO.

27:46.012 --> 27:48.971
OKAY PARTNER, WHAT DO YOU SAY
WE GO HAND OUT SOME FLYERS?

27:49.624 --> 27:51.321
-AND I GOT SOME
DECISIONS TO MAKE.

27:57.023 --> 28:00.156
-[SLOW COUNTRY MUSIC]

28:05.814 --> 28:08.469
-♪ SCHOOL LET OUT
AT 3:00 ♪

28:08.599 --> 28:10.732
♪ AND I PICKED JACKSON UP

28:12.603 --> 28:15.171
♪ I HAD THE TENT AND
THE SLEEPING BAGS ♪

